...just like he said.

755
00:56:12,870 --> 00:56:15,487
And, just like Norton said...

756
00:56:15,706 --> 00:56:17,162
...Andy got no answers.

757
00:56:25,382 --> 00:56:30,297
The following April, Andy did tax returns
for half the guards at Shawshank.

758
00:56:31,638 --> 00:56:33,879
Year after that, he did them all...

759
00:56:34,141 --> 00:56:36,052
...Including the warden's.

760
00:56:37,811 --> 00:56:41,270
Year after that,
they rescheduled the intramural season...

761
00:56:41,481 --> 00:56:43,893
...to coincide with tax season.

762
00:56:45,485 --> 00:56:49,945
The guards on the opposing teams
all remembered to bring their W-2s.

763
00:56:50,157 --> 00:56:53,946
So Moresby Prison issued you a gun,
but you actually paid for it.

764
00:56:54,161 --> 00:56:55,868
Damn right. The holster too.

765
00:56:56,079 --> 00:56:58,537
See, that's tax-deductible.
You can write that off.

766
00:56:58,749 --> 00:57:01,787
Yes, sir.
Andy was a regular cottage industry.

767
00:57:02,502 --> 00:57:06,996
In fact, it got so busy at tax time,
he was allowed a staff.

768
00:57:07,257 --> 00:57:09,715
Could you hand me
a stack of 1040s?

769
00:57:09,927 --> 00:57:14,763
Got me out of the wood shop
a month out of the year, and that was fine.

770
00:57:16,016 --> 00:57:19,179
And still, he kept sending those letters.

771
00:57:22,940 --> 00:57:25,773
Red. Red. Andy.

772
00:57:25,943 --> 00:57:26,978
It's Brooks.

773
00:57:28,111 --> 00:57:29,601
Watch the door.

774
00:57:29,863 --> 00:57:31,194
Please, Brooks.

775
00:57:31,365 --> 00:57:33,231
- Calm the fuck down.
- Stay back!

776
00:57:33,700 --> 00:57:35,816
- Stay back, goddamn it!
- What's going on?

777
00:57:35,994 --> 00:57:39,032
You tell me. One second he's fine,
then out come the knife.

778
00:57:39,206 --> 00:57:41,072
Brooks. We can talk about this, right?

779
00:57:41,249 --> 00:57:45,083
There's nothing to talk about.
I'll cut his fucking throat.

780
00:57:45,379 --> 00:57:47,086
What's he done to you?

781
00:57:47,297 --> 00:57:48,958
It's what they done!

782
00:57:49,466 --> 00:57:50,706
I got no choice.

783
00:57:51,218 --> 00:57:53,505
Brooks, you won't hurt Heywood.
We all know that.

784
00:57:53,720 --> 00:57:56,178
- Right, Heywood?
- Sure. I know that.

785
00:57:56,390 --> 00:57:59,724
He's a friend of yours,
and Brooks is a reasonable man.

786
00:57:59,893 --> 00:58:01,884
- Right, guys?
- Yes.

787
00:58:02,062 --> 00:58:04,554
So put the knife down.
Brooks, look at me.

788
00:58:04,731 --> 00:58:08,725
Put the knife down. Brooks.

789
00:58:08,986 --> 00:58:11,068
Look at his neck, for God's sake.

790
00:58:11,822 --> 00:58:14,154
Look at his neck. He's bleeding.

791
00:58:15,075 --> 00:58:16,531
It's the only--

792
00:58:16,743 --> 00:58:18,780
It's the only way they'd let me stay.

793
00:58:19,079 --> 00:58:21,411
Come on, this is crazy.
You don't want to do this.

794
00:58:21,665 --> 00:58:23,747
Put it-- Put it down.

795
00:58:31,091 --> 00:58:34,004
Hey. Hey. Take it easy.

796
00:58:34,678 --> 00:58:36,260
You'll be all right.

797
00:58:36,430 --> 00:58:38,888
Him? What about me?

798
00:58:39,099 --> 00:58:41,466
Crazy old fool damn near cut my throat!

799
00:58:41,685 --> 00:58:43,596
You've had worse from shaving.

800
00:58:43,770 --> 00:58:45,511
What did you do to set him off?

801
00:58:45,689 --> 00:58:48,306
Nothing. I come in here to say farewell.

802
00:58:48,942 --> 00:58:51,604
Ain't you heard?
His parole's come through.

803
00:58:53,780 --> 00:58:56,738
I just don't understand
what happened in there, that's all.

804
00:58:56,908 --> 00:58:59,741
Old man's crazy as a rat
in a tin shithouse.

805
00:58:59,953 --> 00:59:01,819
Oh, Heywood, that's enough out of you.

806
00:59:02,039 --> 00:59:04,781
- Heard he had you shitting in your pants.
- Fuck you.

807
00:59:05,042 --> 00:59:06,248
Knock it off.

808
00:59:07,210 --> 00:59:08,621
Brooks ain't no bug.

809
00:59:08,962 --> 00:59:10,623
He's just--

810
00:59:12,466 --> 00:59:14,252
He's just institutionalized.

811
00:59:15,635 --> 00:59:17,546
"Institutionalized," my ass.

812
00:59:17,763 --> 00:59:21,757
The man's been in here 50 years,
Heywood, 50 years!

813
00:59:21,975 --> 00:59:23,682
This is all he knows.

814
00:59:23,894 --> 00:59:26,181
In here, he's an important man...

815
00:59:26,396 --> 00:59:27,477
...an educated man.

816
00:59:28,315 --> 00:59:30,226
Outside, he's nothing.

817
00:59:31,109 --> 00:59:34,602
Just a used-up con
with arthritis in both hands.

818
00:59:34,821 --> 00:59:37,813
Probably couldn't get a library card
if he tried.

819
00:59:38,075 --> 00:59:39,816
You know what I'm trying to say?

820
00:59:40,077 --> 00:59:42,990
I do believe
you're talking out of your ass.

821
00:59:44,247 --> 00:59:46,488
You believe whatever you want.

822
00:59:47,084 --> 00:59:49,496
But I tell you these walls are funny.

823
00:59:51,088 --> 00:59:52,749
First you hate them.

824
00:59:54,591 --> 00:59:56,502
Then you get used to them.

825
00:59:58,428 --> 01:00:00,419
Enough time passes...

826
01:00:01,098 --> 01:00:03,089
...you get so you depend on them.

827
01:00:04,101 --> 01:00:06,308
That's "institutionalized."

828
01:00:06,520 --> 01:00:10,764
- Shit. I could never get like that.
- Oh, yeah?

829
01:00:11,650 --> 01:00:14,142
Wait till you've been here
as long as Brooks.

830
01:00:14,361 --> 01:00:15,943
Goddamn right.

831
01:00:18,532 --> 01:00:20,443
They send you here for life...

832
01:00:21,118 --> 01:00:23,450
...that's exactly what they take.

833
01:00:25,205 --> 01:00:27,196
Part that counts, anyway.

834
01:00:34,798 --> 01:00:37,711
I can't take care of you no more, Jake.

835
01:00:38,885 --> 01:00:40,546
You go on now.

836
01:00:41,805 --> 01:00:43,295
You're free.

837
01:00:44,558 --> 01:00:46,140
You're free.

838
01:01:02,450 --> 01:01:04,987
Bye. Joe?

839
01:01:05,162 --> 01:01:06,823
Good luck, Brooksie.

840
01:01:09,124 --> 01:01:11,206
Take care of yourself, Brooks.

841
01:01:44,784 --> 01:01:46,274
Dear fellas:

842
01:01:46,578 --> 01:01:50,788
I can't believe how fast things move
on the outside.

843
01:01:52,083 --> 01:01:54,745
Watch it, old-timer! Want to get killed?

844
01:01:55,962 --> 01:01:59,455
[Saw an automobile once
when I was a kid...

845
01:02:00,133 --> 01:02:02,545
...but now they're everywhere.

846
01:02:06,223 --> 01:02:10,512
The world went and got itself
in a big damn hurry.

847
01:02:26,326 --> 01:02:30,115
The parole board
got me into this halfway house...

848
01:02:30,413 --> 01:02:32,074
...called "The Brewer"...

849
01:02:32,290 --> 01:02:33,451
...and a job...

850
01:02:33,667 --> 01:02:36,625
...bagging groceries at the Food-Way.

851
01:02:38,171 --> 01:02:40,583
It's hard work and I try to keep up...

852
01:02:40,799 --> 01:02:43,166
...but my hands hurt most of the time.

853
01:02:43,468 --> 01:02:48,338
Make sure your man double-bags.
Last time, the bottom near came out.

854
01:02:48,515 --> 01:02:51,257
Make sure you double-bag
like the lady says. Understand?

855
01:02:51,476 --> 01:02:52,841
Yes, sir. Surely will.

856
01:02:53,019 --> 01:02:56,557
I don't think the store manager
likes me very much.

857
01:02:59,567 --> 01:03:03,856
Sometimes after work,
I go to the park and feed the birds.

858
01:03:04,322 --> 01:03:05,812
I keep thinking...

859
01:03:06,032 --> 01:03:09,366
...Jake might just show up
and say hello.

860
01:03:09,995 --> 01:03:11,986
But he never does.

861
01:03:13,206 --> 01:03:18,042
I hope, wherever he is, he's doing okay
and making new friends.

862
01:03:21,673 --> 01:03:24,381
I have trouble sleeping at night.

863
01:03:24,718 --> 01:03:27,961
I have bad dreams, like I'm falling.

864
01:03:28,221 --> 01:03:30,462
I wake up scared.

865
01:03:30,682 --> 01:03:34,892
Sometimes it takes me a while
to remember where I am.

866
01:03:36,396 --> 01:03:41,311
Maybe I should get me a gun and rob
the Food-Way so they'd send me home.

867
01:03:41,609 --> 01:03:45,944
I could shoot the manager while
! Was at it. Sort of like a bonus.

868
01:03:47,615 --> 01:03:51,609
I guess I'm too old
for that sort of nonsense anymore.

869
01:03:51,870 --> 01:03:53,577
I don't like it here.

870
01:03:53,788 --> 01:03:57,782
I'm tired of being afraid all the time.
I've decided...

871
01:03:58,626 --> 01:04:00,287
...not to stay.

872
01:04:11,222 --> 01:04:13,759
I doubt they'll kick up any fuss...

873
01:04:13,975 --> 01:04:17,468
...hot for an old crook like me.

874
01:05:19,958 --> 01:05:24,202
"I doubt they'll kick up any fuss,
not for an old crook like me.

875
01:05:25,255 --> 01:05:29,089
P.S. Tell Heywood I'm sorry
I put a knife to his throat.

876
01:05:29,300 --> 01:05:31,632
No hard feelings. Brooks."

877
01:05:42,105 --> 01:05:44,062
He should have died in here.

878
01:05:49,612 --> 01:05:51,023
What the fuck have you done?

879
01:05:51,197 --> 01:05:53,859
It's a goddamn mess,
I'll tell you that.

880
01:05:59,414 --> 01:06:03,157
- What's all this?
- You tell me. They're addressed to you.

881
01:06:04,419 --> 01:06:05,750
Take it.

882
01:06:14,304 --> 01:06:15,794
"Dear Mr. Dufresne:

883
01:06:16,931 --> 01:06:18,888
In response to your repeated inquiries...

884
01:06:19,100 --> 01:06:23,389
...the state has allocated the enclosed
funds for your library project."

885
01:06:24,147 --> 01:06:25,979
This is $200.

886
01:06:26,191 --> 01:06:30,185
"In addition, the library district
has generously responded...

887
01:06:30,403 --> 01:06:32,940
...with a donation of used books
and sundries.

888
01:06:33,156 --> 01:06:37,275
We trust this will fill your needs.
We now consider the matter closed.

889
01:06:37,494 --> 01:06:39,360
Please stop sending us letters."

890
01:06:39,537 --> 01:06:42,199
I want all this cleared out
before the warden gets back.

891
01:06:42,415 --> 01:06:43,576
Yes, sir.

892
01:06:47,879 --> 01:06:49,040
Good for you, Andy.

893
01:06:51,841 --> 01:06:53,252
Wow.

894
01:06:54,344 --> 01:06:56,255
It only took six years.

895
01:06:57,847 --> 01:07:00,589
From now on, I'll write two
letters a week instead of one.

896
01:07:00,767 --> 01:07:04,101
I believe you're crazy enough.
Get this stuff out...

897
01:07:04,395 --> 01:07:06,807
...like he said.
I've got to pinch a loaf.

898
01:07:07,023 --> 01:07:08,479
When I come back...

899
01:07:08,691 --> 01:07:10,432
...this is all gone, all right?

900
01:07:59,200 --> 01:08:00,611
Do you hear that?

901
01:09:09,604 --> 01:09:12,813
Dufresne! Dufresne!

902
01:09:13,066 --> 01:09:14,556
Andy, let me out!

903
01:09:21,449 --> 01:09:26,410
I have no idea to this day what those
two Italian ladies were singing about.

904
01:09:26,704 --> 01:09:28,911
Truth is, I don't want to know.

905
01:09:29,123 --> 01:09:31,615
Some things are best left unsaid.

906
01:09:35,213 --> 01:09:37,921
! Like to think it was something
so beautiful...

907
01:09:38,132 --> 01:09:40,248
...It can't be expressed in words...

908
01:09:40,468 --> 01:09:43,381
...and makes your heart ache
because of it.

909
01:09:45,056 --> 01:09:47,548
I tell you, those voices soared...

910
01:09:47,809 --> 01:09:52,098
...higher and farther than anybody
in a gray place dares to dream.

911
01:09:52,313 --> 01:09:55,681
It was like a beautiful bird
flapped into our drab cage...

912
01:09:55,900 --> 01:09:58,642
...and made those walls dissolve away.

913
01:09:59,112 --> 01:10:01,274
And for the briefest of moments...

914
01:10:01,489 --> 01:10:04,481
...every last man at Shawshank felt free.

915
01:10:07,078 --> 01:10:09,740
It pissed the warden off
something awful.

916
01:10:11,040 --> 01:10:12,030
Open the door.

917
01:10:14,961 --> 01:10:16,702
Open it up!

918
01:10:18,005 --> 01:10:20,747
Dufresne, open this door!

919
01:10:22,093 --> 01:10:23,299
Turn that off!

920
01:10:30,351 --> 01:10:32,809
I am warning you. Turn that off!

921
01:10:46,659 --> 01:10:48,570
Dufresne.

922
01:10:50,538 --> 01:10:52,074
You're mine now.

923
01:10:59,505 --> 01:11:02,748
Andy got two weeks in the hole
for that little stunt.

924
01:11:02,967 --> 01:11:04,549
On your feet.

925
01:11:05,720 --> 01:11:08,132
- Hey, look who's here.
- Maestro!

926
01:11:08,306 --> 01:11:09,512
Hey.

927
01:11:09,891 --> 01:11:13,555
You couldn't play something good, huh?
Like Hank Williams?

928
01:11:13,895 --> 01:11:16,683
They broke the door down
before I could take requests.

929
01:11:16,898 --> 01:11:20,016
- Was it worth two weeks?
- Easiest time I ever did.

930
01:11:20,234 --> 01:11:22,566
No such thing as easy time in the hole.

931
01:11:22,737 --> 01:11:24,444
A week in the hole is like a year.

932
01:11:24,655 --> 01:11:27,943
- Damn straight.
- I had Mr. Mozart to keep me company.

933
01:11:28,159 --> 01:11:31,117
So they let you tote
that record player down there, huh?

934
01:11:33,539 --> 01:11:34,904
It was in here.

935
01:11:35,750 --> 01:11:36,990
In here.

936
01:11:38,127 --> 01:11:40,209
That's the beauty of music. They...

937
01:11:40,421 --> 01:11:42,753
...can't get that from you.

938
01:11:46,302 --> 01:11:48,669
Haven't you ever felt
that way about music?

939
01:11:50,473 --> 01:11:53,591
Well, I played a mean harmonica
as a younger man.

940
01:11:54,644 --> 01:11:56,351
Lost interest in it, though.

941
01:11:56,562 --> 01:11:58,144
Didn't make much sense in here.

942
01:11:58,481 --> 01:12:00,472
Here's where it makes the most sense.

943
01:12:01,025 --> 01:12:03,062
You need it so you don't forget.

944
01:12:03,653 --> 01:12:04,939
Forget?

945
01:12:05,238 --> 01:12:08,321
Forget that there are...

946
01:12:08,533 --> 01:12:09,944
...places...

947
01:12:10,451 --> 01:12:14,285
...in the world
that aren't made out of stone.

948
01:12:15,289 --> 01:12:16,779
There's something...

949
01:12:17,124 --> 01:12:18,535
...inside...

950
01:12:18,793 --> 01:12:20,750
...that they can't get to...

951
01:12:20,962 --> 01:12:22,373
...that they can't touch.

952
01:12:22,880 --> 01:12:24,291
That's yours.

953
01:12:25,842 --> 01:12:27,424
What are you talking about?

954
01:12:28,469 --> 01:12:29,709
Hope.

955
01:12:30,763 --> 01:12:32,094
Hope.

956
01:12:34,058 --> 01:12:36,049
Let me tell you something, my friend.

957
01:12:36,853 --> 01:12:39,140
Hope is a dangerous thing.

958
01:12:40,314 --> 01:12:42,646
Hope can drive a man insane.

959
01:12:43,401 --> 01:12:45,517
It's got no use on the inside.

960
01:12:45,736 --> 01:12:47,943
You'd better get used to that idea.

961
01:12:50,449 --> 01:12:51,939
Like Brooks did?

962
01:13:17,310 --> 01:13:18,300
Sit down.

963
01:13:23,649 --> 01:13:26,937
Says here that you've served
30 years of a life sentence.

964
01:13:28,112 --> 01:13:30,149
You feel you've been rehabilitated?

965
01:13:30,364 --> 01:13:31,604
Oh, yes, sir.

966
01:13:32,867 --> 01:13:34,198
Without a doubt.

967
01:13:35,369 --> 01:13:37,781
I can honestly say I'm a changed man.

968
01:13:39,790 --> 01:13:41,701
No danger to society here.

969
01:13:42,251 --> 01:13:43,787
God's honest truth.

970
01:13:46,339 --> 01:13:48,455
Absolutely rehabilitated.

971
01:13:58,434 --> 01:13:59,765
Thirty years.

972
01:14:01,729 --> 01:14:03,640
Jesus, when you say it like that...

973
01:14:04,523 --> 01:14:06,309
You wonder where it went.

974
01:14:08,736 --> 01:14:10,898
I wonder where 10 years went.

975
01:14:15,868 --> 01:14:16,903
Here.

976
01:14:17,370 --> 01:14:20,078
A little parole-rejection present.

977
01:14:21,374 --> 01:14:23,035
Go ahead and open it.

978
01:14:24,168 --> 01:14:26,205
Went through one of your competitors.

979
01:14:26,379 --> 01:14:29,542
I hope you don't mind.
I wanted it to be a surprise.

980
01:14:39,558 --> 01:14:41,048
It's very pretty.

981
01:14:42,770 --> 01:14:43,976
Thank you.

982
01:14:46,565 --> 01:14:48,021
You going to play it?

983
01:14:52,571 --> 01:14:53,857
No.

984
01:14:57,451 --> 01:14:58,862
Not right now.

985
01:15:16,554 --> 01:15:17,635
Roll in!

986
01:15:53,841 --> 01:15:55,081
Lights out!

987
01:16:29,668 --> 01:16:31,830
Andy was as good as his word.

988
01:16:32,171 --> 01:16:34,959
He wrote two letters a week
instead of one.

989
01:16:37,009 --> 01:16:41,128
In 1959, the state senate
finally clued in to the fact...

990
01:16:41,347 --> 01:16:44,510
...they couldn't buy him off
with just a $200 check.

991
01:16:44,683 --> 01:16:49,018
Appropriations Committee
voted an annual payment of $500...

992
01:16:49,188 --> 01:16:51,099
...just to shut him up.

993
01:16:51,315 --> 01:16:54,307
And you'd be amazed how far
Andy could stretch it.

994
01:16:54,527 --> 01:16:57,440
He made deals with book clubs,
charity groups.

995
01:16:57,655 --> 01:17:00,397
He bought remaindered books
by the pound...

996
01:17:00,908 --> 01:17:02,444
"Treasure Island.â€

997
01:17:02,993 --> 01:17:04,324
Robert Louis--

998
01:17:04,537 --> 01:17:05,527
Stevenson.

999
01:17:05,746 --> 01:17:07,157
Fiction, adventure.

1000
01:17:09,708 --> 01:17:10,743
What's next?

1001
01:17:10,918 --> 01:17:14,001
I got here Auto Repair...

1002
01:17:14,713 --> 01:17:15,874
...and Soap Carving.

1003
01:17:16,090 --> 01:17:19,333
Trade skills and hobbies.
Under "Educational," behind you.

1004
01:17:19,552 --> 01:17:21,384
"Count of Monte Crisco."

1005
01:17:21,887 --> 01:17:24,174
That's "Cristo,"â€ you dumb-shit.

1006
01:17:25,266 --> 01:17:26,256
By Alexandree...

1007
01:17:26,725 --> 01:17:28,011
...Dum-ass.

1008
01:17:28,352 --> 01:17:29,387
